Flashback Friday: October 27, 2015, through October 27, 2022

Vulnerability post here. Scroll if you don’t have anything nice to say and if this may trigger you. 

Sometimes I look at older pictures of myself, and I don’t recognize myself. And it's not that I don’t think I wasn’t attractive in 2015, but I looked exhausted 😩 and always felt the need to prove myself. 

At this point, I was chasing down the Ironman World Championship dream, doing two Ironmans a year, building my business and brand, and drinking wine almost every night (later on December 7th).

Now I see photos of myself from the last year and especially the previous two months, and this is what I see:

😊 Happy
💪🏼 Healthy
👎🏼 Alcohol-Free. 
👏🏼 No need to prove shit to anyone and myself (Huge, Big!)
♥️ Living a life for me. 

Sure, I had to make some significant changes for myself, but it has been 💯 percent worth it. 

These photos popped up on my phone, and I showed them to my friends yesterday, and they said, “That’s not even you, Jen,” and I got a little emotional. 

Posting more this week due to a significant shift that I made in my life three years ago. Maybe I can help others. 

Love 💕 
Jen

Why Did You Make A Change and Move to Costa Rica 🇨🇷?

If I had $100 for every time, someone asked that, my rent would have been paid for a year down here! 

But in all seriousness, let me explain. 

I have been coming to Costa Rica 🇨🇷 since 2019, and I fell in love. I fell in love with the beaches, the community, the culture, the food, the animals, and the landscape. And so many more thoughts 💭 of why. 

I also went through a personal change and am still not ready to chat about that, but those that know, know. No, I wasn’t running away from the life that I know.

I was running back to the girl that I was meant to be. Don’t let society change the ways how you look at things. I know it doesn’t make sense to a lot of people. And that’s ok; it’s not their life. 

They don’t need to understand. They need to support and love 💕 you—a pretty simple task. 

If you are up to the task, I open you with arms open; if not, there is the door 🚪! 

And this is why I moved to Costa Rica 🇨🇷!

#swimmingsaturday makes sense today, as I want to chat about OWS, open water swimming!⁠
⁠
A couple of days ago, I took two ladies out in #playasamara for a swim. We swam from Matapalo Beach into Samara, by Gusto Beach. ⁠
⁠
I have swum in open water in oceans from Costa Rica to Hawaii to Florida and California, and it can be challenging vs. swimming in a lake, which is where I grew up. ⁠
⁠
Here are a couple of tips for you that can help you as you start working on your OWS in the ocean:⁠
⁠
🌊 Ideally, look for objects higher than eye levels, such as a building or a tower. Something that isn’t moving. ⁠
🏊🏼‍♀️ When doing the front crawl, I try to breathe every 5 - 6 breaths before I sighted off my object.⁠
😮‍💨 When I take a breath, I will look straight up to get my breath and then go back to swimming. ⁠
🌊 If you are dealing with tides, ideally, get past the break during low tide so that you can swim in calmer waters. ⁠
⁠

“It’s so fun to live on purpose.” ~ Abraham Hicks

I chatted with you yesterday about routines, and I heard this quote today during my coffee/hammock time.

My whole life, I always knew what I would do, whether it was working with marine mammals, qualifying for the Ironman World Championship, or recently moving to Costa Rica 🇨🇷. And many people are asking me how I did it.

Here are three thoughts that I have about making a BIG move:

😮 Being on vacation is WAY different than living here. Make sure you come here for longer than a week and do not stay in a hotel. Find an Air BnB or an apartment and give yourself at least 7 - 8 weeks if you can pull it out. 
🛍 Make sure you can live without a car for a while, have no easy access to Amazon and a shopping mall, and realize that they may not have the “normal” things you love at your grocery store. (I miss Kerry Gold Butter and Fage Greek Yogurt.) 
🇨🇷 Why are you moving? Are you starting a new journey? Are you running away from the problems that you are currently dealing with? Because those problems will still be there in a different country. 

When I heard that quote this morning, I thought, “I am living on MY purpose.” And I chose to be happy. 

God, am I freaking happy, but I had to find it from within. Not from another state or country,  not more materialistic sh%^ but from within.

Once you find that purpose, life comes pretty naturally to you. Thoughts?

Love you 😘 and scroll 👈🏼 to enjoy the last 24 hours and don't forget to share and save these tips! 
Jen

Today, I chatted about tips on how to manage your time. We ALL have 24 hours a day, but it is how you use them. I shared five tips for you but here is probably one of my favorite ones:

“Focus on What You Like”

If you enjoy a particular workout, you will enjoy it. If you love running, you run. If you hate it and signed up for a 5k or a marathon because you want to drop weight or accomplish a big goal, then maybe that isn’t the best way to look at it. 

I love my workouts with @samara_fit_ and @soulfitsa (when I am in town). I love going for walks on the beach, swimming in the ocean, and running back from town. I love HIIT workouts on my porch or the beach. I look forward to these workouts. 

Find out what YOU love 💕 and those workouts will come naturally to you. 

I promise.

I have some news for you, and you won't believe this!⁠
⁠
As an endurance athlete, you will NOT get bulky like a weightlifter, but you will get strong! I have heard this numerous times:⁠
⁠
”Coach Jen, I don’t want to get bulky like a weightlifter.” ⁠
Let’s talk about Exercise Physiology and understanding the principle of overload and specificity.⁠
⁠
🏃‍♀️ Principle of Overload: Overloading a system will cause it to respond and adapt. For example, the more you run, your body will get used to running. Likewise, the more you lift, the more your body will get used to lifting more weight.⁠
⁠
🏋🏼‍♀️ Principle of Specificity: Muscles will adapt specifically to what exercise you are doing. For example, if you train your leg muscles, they will hypertrophy (get bigger), and your shoulder muscles won't.⁠
⁠
🦋 YOUR Takeaway: As an endurance athlete, you will be running, swimming, and cycling WAY more than lifting. If you are an everyday human, who wants a beautiful balance of lifting and cardio, I suggest figuring out a routine of what works best for you, your schedule, and your happiness.⁠
⁠
I have worked with many triathletes, runners, and cyclists in the gym who wanted to add strength training to their schedule but didn’t know how. In San Antonio, I coached Bootcamps for @amorcyclingstudio and had a class called “The Strongest Mile,” which was strength training specific for endurance athletes. ⁠

Amidst the lush beauty of Costa Rica, I found solace in the simple act of walking. Each step became a meditation, a rhythm syncing with the heartbeat of my healing heart.

Reflecting on this journey, I realize that healing isn’t a destination; it’s a continuous exploration of self. Strength training, walks, and surfing have been my companions, helping me rediscover the resilient spirit within.
